##I'm okay as long as I don't get sick

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews carried out by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups in the epidemic situation and their needs, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we've put together a list to share with you.

Deep breathing in case of an outbreak
A case study of the migrant workers'families in difficulty (13)

I'm fine, as long as I don't get sick
DICTATION: a Jian (alias) / Jiangxi nationality
Place of employment: Zhuhai

Editor's Note: A Jian, 37, is single. 16-year-old migrant workers, came to Zhuhai for five years, is now an electronics factory in Zhuhai, a general storekeeper. In order to take better care of his elderly parents, A-jian took them to his side, at the same time, he also took care of the nephew left after his brother's death. The family lives in a rented house in the Zhuhai Industrial Park.
I take care of my family, and sometimes I get lost

I've been working here for over 20 years. In 2004, he went to work in the Guangdong Shunde Hardware Factory. After the Shunde Factory moved to Zhuhai, he worked in the Zhuhai Electronics Factory. Began to go out to work with relatives, relatives back home, I left alone in Zhuhai.

When my brother died in a car accident in 2014, my sister-in-law left my nephew, Xiaojun (not his real name) , when he was very young, to start a new family, and rarely came back. My family kept it a secret from gene, saying, "daddy went to work far away and will never come back. " But there was also some awareness, every time I asked, the family would not let me ask... in order not to affect the children, i let Jun and his grandparents together to live in Zhuhai.

On January 16,2020, I read about the new pneumonia on my cell phone, but I found it before anyone else at work. I have a colleague in Hubei, I told him, your side found 66 cases of new coronary pneumonia, colleagues do not know what it is, after a few days after the very bad spread. I didn't take it seriously at first, but my relatives called to say how bad it was and told everyone not to go out, as if something terrible was going to happen. I was planning to go back to my hometown, but I thought of what they said, "at this age, I haven't earned any money (I owe my relatives over 100,000 yuan in foreign debt) , and I am ashamed to go back. " I don't want to go back, either. I alone take care of two old people, and children, sometimes will feel more lonely, very confused.

A-JIAN's nephew Jun (2019)

My nephew Xiaojun, before more cheerful, every home after school is also willing to communicate with us. But now do not know how, more silent and withdrawn, but also more and more unwilling to do with us to communicate too much, academic performance is also a lot of retrogression. During the outbreak, two elderly people at Home Care Xiaojun, but the elderly also can not help Xiaojun homework, Xiaojun did not have a little online class began to play games, grandma and GRANDPA said also do not listen. I usually go home after work to find out about Jun's study. If I ask Jun if he can do it, he can answer it, but every time he does his homework, he writes it wrong. Sometimes when I ask Jun a question, he doesn't answer it either, i couldn't help but curse gene (talk to him loudly) . I'm also worried that Jun won't be able to keep up with his studies. I'm not married and I have no children, only my brother.
Now I have to do a lot of work by myself, there will be psychological pressure

Even though the outbreak is spreading, I've been back at work since February 10th. Migrant workers are now temporarily unable to work, need to declare health every day, can not concentrate on eating, need to take regular temperature, enter the factory also need to measure, also need to spray disinfection water. They can not be isolated at home alone, they need to be isolated in a separate layer of factory dormitories.

Collaborator Social Worker visits a Jian's family (2019)

My colleague in Hubei is unable to come to work, other colleagues are now each other cover. Now I work to increase the affairs of colleagues in Hubei, I have not done before, now feel more helpless, very afraid, uneasy mood, worried about not doing well, the leadership will urge. In the past, someone was responsible for the storage, usually I was only responsible for the ingredients, now a lot of work needs to bear up. It's more work, but the pay is the same. There will be psychological pressure, do not know how to do.

The factory notice said that if you don't report to the factory on February 20, you don't have to come back. Although there was no formal talk of layoffs, this was tantamount to a disguised layoff. Now the order is not much, also needs to reduce the staff policy, possibly next month I will be transferred to the workshop to work. If transferred to the workshop work, is no position, I worry to the workshop can not complete the work, after all, the warehouse and the production line is not the same. I'm still a little worried about doing this day by day.

If the layoff can compensate part of the salary, hope can be laid off, can do other work. But after more than 10 years in the factory, I couldn't bear it, I was laid off, and I didn't know what to do. Some students also told me to work at home, but back to the old people's body also have to take care of, income is not high, more difficult to mix, or in Zhuhai to see.
As long as I don't get sick

Go home is sooner or later to go back, but in the old people out to dinner more on time, the climate also feels good. Other expenses in the home can not be less, now have a job in Zhuhai, also will maintain some expenses, money like water can flow, go back and forth. Relatives back home can lend you money, and you haven't paid them back yet. I don't know what I'm GonNa do back home, I don't have a plan, I just go with the flow. It's not convenient to run around Zhuhai and my hometown, and I don't own the factory, so I can ask for leave if I want to.

I am more worried about the old man's health, illness is a sudden disaster, no source of livelihood is difficult to maintain. Two old people also have some diseases, my father suffered from cerebral hemorrhage and gastric ulcer, my mother's eyes are not good, they generally do not go to the nearby Three-a hospital to see a doctor, where the suspicion is expensive, and pit people, will take the bus to the far hospital to see a doctor. If anything happens, I won't be able to come to work, and I'll have to take care of them. The worst thing you can do is go to the hospital. You could run out of money in a year.

A Jian's father takes a medicine for stomach ulcers (photo taken in 2019) 

Now my situation is good, if encounter worse situation still do not know can persist to live, after all, I am a person, what wind and grass is also very difficult, will be more confused. I often say that I do not have an ideal life, you lack what you think is the most important. It's not about the money, it's about the body. But you really don't have any money. You can't beat a hero with a dime. No good body no money and can not maintain, when you do not have money you will feel the most important money, when you are sick, you think you do not want money, a good body on it. My family's counting on me right now, as long as I don't get sick.

Social Worker's notes

During the interview, A-jian made light of his brother's sudden death, but his words could still feel his pressure, loneliness, and confusion. He alone shouldered the burden of his family, supported the elderly and his nephew... the sudden epidemic, he didn't know what would happen if things got worse. He said he didn't have a dream, but he took on the life of his family. He worked hard for this, all he asked was "not to get sick" . These do not seem to have ideal words, in fact, permeated everywhere in the face of the resilience of suffering. Let's pay our respects to Ken.

Follow-up advice

Now:
1. Jun is invited to participate in the online classroom homework tutoring, interest classes and other online services.
2. Follow up the work of a Jian, timely psychological counseling to ease the pressure of work and life.
LONG-TERM:

1. Continue to invite accompanying Angel Volunteers to participate in Xiaojun accompanying service, and coordinate experts in psychological counseling to carry out case service.
2. Invite A-jian to participate in the service of volunteers, young workers, broaden their interpersonal circle, and enhance their resilience and self-confidence in the face of difficulties.
3. Assisting kin in career planning.
4. Regular visits, visits to the elderly, and coordination of medical volunteer support.
